
[1]unguarded

   UNGU'ARDED, a.

   1. Not guarded; not watched.

   2. Not defended; having no guard.

   3. Careless; negligent; not attentive to danger; not cautious; as, to
   be unguarded in conversation.

   4. Negligently said or done; not done or spoken with caution; as an
   unguarded expression or action.
